	<Title>
		Sodium: Smarten up
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;Ready to take a step toward heart-healthy eating? Reduce the amount of sodium in your diet. Scale back without sending your taste buds into a panic: 1. Add spices or flavorings to your food instead of salt. Try salt-free seasoning blends. 2. Don&apos;t add salt when cooking rice, pasta or hot cereal. 3. Rinse canned foods, such as tuna, to remove some sodium. 4. Buy foods labeled &quot;no salt added,&quot; &quot;sodium-free,&quot; &quot;low sodium&quot; or &quot;very low sodium.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;
